The paper deals with the construction of cyclic codes using cyclotomic sequences, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The codes are also used in data transmission technologies and computer applications, which fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and distributed systems (cs.DS), respectively. The paper also mentions the computation of difference sets, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and number theory (cs.NT). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of encoding and decoding algorithms, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SI).
